{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9588f682-5762-4e35-b838-8eb3e7b18bd3","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 3.x → 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **4.0.0**, the SDK exclusively targets **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `dotnet test` runner) and no longer ships the VSTest adapter/runner. This means `vstest.console.exe` can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n   This uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively — no extra config needed.\n\n2. **Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   and referencing the VSTest bridge package — but Microsoft recommends migrating away from `vstest.console` entirely.\n\nThe cleanest fix is option 1: replace `vstest.console` with `dotnet test` in your pipeline. Want me to update anything?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"14773eb2-0e02-4143-9427-c22a18455a1a","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"4C1A:36154C:C587B0:F0EF74:6A014803"},"id":"303dfdc7-c8e9-42ec-b904-60308ee7cc8b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T03:07:54.950Z","parentId":"d893daa8-02e2-44cd-8d3e-13276312cd6b"}
